      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-disc-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) computed across three systematically refined meshes (3.2M, 9.1M, 25.6M cells). GCI for hemolysis index QoI: 4.2% on fine mesh, well within the 10% acceptance threshold. y+ < 1 maintained on blood-contacting surfaces. Exceeds MRL 2 requirement; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions replicate clinical CPB operating range: flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–4000 RPM, blood analog fluid (glycerol-water 36% by mass) at 37°C. Five operating points bracket the worst-case hemolysis region. Boundary conditions documented and traceable to ISO 14708-5 and FDA guidance on blood pump testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by CFD compared against bench-top measurements across all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error 8.3%, maximum error 14.1%. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 correctly identified at 4 of 5 operating points. Comparison metrics documented in validation report VR-OC-2024-02 with full uncertainty budgets."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH). Both are directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Secondary QoIs include shear stress exposure time and volume-averaged shear rate, which are mechanistically linked to the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law model used in the simulation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/morrison-val-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under the same 5 flow-speed combinations used in the COU. Blood analog fluid properties match simulation inputs. Validation domain (pump geometry, operating envelope, hemolysis QoI) is directly representative of the COU decision context. No extrapolation beyond validated operating range required."
    },
    {
